en_812710_0	Major General Mahinda Mudalige of the Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) assumed duties as the new Commander, Security Forces - West on Wednesday (10) in a formal ceremony.
en_812710_1	The newly-appointed SF commander was welcomed in a Guard Turnout and a Guard of Honour on arrival at the HQ premises in Panagoda.
en_812710_2	Subsequently, Major General Mudalige signed an official document amid religious observances of all faiths.
en_812710_3	He also planted a sapling in the premises to mark the day's event.
en_812710_4	An All Rank tea culminated the proceedings.
en_812710_5	He succeeded Major General Sathyapriya Liyanage who has been appointed the Commandant Sri Lanka Army Volunteer Force & Commanding Officer of Overall Operation Command.
en_812710_6	General Officer Commanding, 14 Division, Brigade Commanders and Commanding Officers of under command establishments attended the venue.
